Size options: 12"x16" frameable limited edition (of 50) print or 5"x7" greeting cards including envelopes.

description:

The text is various words associated with Christmas: Jesus, tree, joy, gifts, Bethlehem, etc.

This artwork is a giclée print; the inks and paper are archival. The original is gouache, Prismacolor pencils, and Pigma pen on Arches textwove paper.

Size options: 12"x16" frameable limited edition (of 50) print or 5"x7" greeting cards including envelopes.

name: Peace on Earth Wreath
description:
*THIS ARTWORK DOES NOT COME FRAMED.

The text reads: "Peace on earth/Goodwill to men" in four styles of lettering.

This artwork is a giclée print; the inks and paper are archival. The original is watercolor, acrylic, Prismacolor pencils, Pigma pen, shell gold (23 karat), and patent gold (23 karat) on Arches textwove paper.

Size options: 12"x16" frameable limited edition (of 50) print or 5"x7" greeting cards including envelopes.

name: Oh, Come, Let Us Adore Him
description:
*THIS ARTWORK DOES NOT COME FRAMED.

This artwork is a giclée print; the inks and paper are archival.  The piece is 18x24” and each one is signed and numbered out of 500 by the artist.  This piece is the first in a series of Christmas carols and features the lyrics to “Oh, Come, All Ye Faithful.”  Included with the piece is a sheet explaining the symbols used in it. The original is gouache, acrylic, pigma pens, and 23 karat patent gold leaf on Arches hot press.

name: Our Doubts
description:
*THIS ARTWORK DOES NOT COME FRAMED.

The text reads:  "Our doubts are traitors and make us lose the good we oft might win by fearing to attempt."  --William Shakespeare   

This artwork is a giclée print; the inks and paper are archival. The piece is 12"x36” and each one is signed and numbered out of 40 by the artist. The original is gouache and Pigma pen on Arches 90 lb. hot press paper.

name: When Obedience Ceases...
description:
*THIS ARTWORK DOES NOT COME FRAMED.

The text reads:  "When obedience ceases to be an irritant and becomes a quest, in that moment, God will endow us with power."  —Ezra Taft Benson

This artwork is a giclée print; the inks and paper are archival. The original is gouache, sumi ink, walnut ink, Prismacolor pen, Pigma pen, and Gansi white on Arches 140 lb. hot press paper.

Size options: 12"x18" frameable print or 5"x7" greeting cards including envelopes. The greeting cards are also giclee prints and are suitable for framing.

name: Sabbath Day
description:
The text reads:  "And that thou mayest more fully keep thyself unspotted from the world, thou shalt go to the house of prayer and offer up thy sacraments upon my holy day . . . that thy joy may be full."  Doctrine and Covenants 59:9, 13.  "The Sabbath Day is given throughout the generations of man for a perpetual covenant.  It is a sign between the Lord and his children forever.  It is a day in which to worship and to express our gratitude and appreciation to the Lord.  It is a day on which to surrender every worldly interest and to praise the Lord humbly.  It is a day not for affliction and burden but for rest and righteous enjoyment."  Spencer W. Kimball

This work was also done in Spanish. 

This artwork is a giclée print; the inks and paper are archival.  The original works are walnut ink, gouache, Prismacolor pen, and Prismacolor pencils on Arches 90 lb. hot press watercolor paper.  It comes with an explanation of all the symbols used in the piece.

Size option:  11"x14" framable print

name: "Happy Girls are Prettiest"
description: Remind your little girls that a smile is their best asset by having this Audrey Hepburn quote hang in their room, bathroom, or any room in your home. This is a 19"(w) x 13.75"(h) hand painted wooden sign. The wood is distressed fence boards. This sign features Amy's daughters favorite colors but upon ordering you can either request this particular sign or choose colors of your own. If you choose colors of your own shipping can take up to three weeks.

name: Leaf Cascade Wreath
description: Watch the leaves fall everyday with this brilliantly colored fall creation. The leaves cascade down its' grape vine wreath base. Accentuated by maroon berries, peek-a-boo pine cones, and finished with a bright orange burlap bow.

name: Spring Fling Wreath
description: Handmade burlap rosettes and leaves rest in the bottom left hand bend of this grape vine wreath to create a simply wonderful everyday wreath. This wreath comes with a monogram option. Colors of the flowers can be requested; however, it will take up to three weeks to ship.

name: Fall On Fire Wreath
description: Bring the vivid colors of fall to life through this beautiful Simple Statements wreath. It features a grape vine wreath dressed up with bright, tri-colored berries and a large burlap bow.

name: Brown Peacock Wreath
description: Class has come again to Fall through this elegant wreath. Adorning this simple grape vine wreath are beautiful slim, light brown feathers that encircle a duo of gold a copper berries and finished with a black and tan checkered bow.

name: A Very Oval Christmas Wreath
description:
Jump into the festive season with a new outlook on decorating. Stepping out of the box, this wreath provides an elegant bravado for your door. With its' thin pine needles to its' maroon berries, white tipped pine cones, large maroon burlap bow, and eccentric oblong shape this wreath is sure to impress.

*This item will ship within one week of order being placed.

name: Classical Christmas Wreath
description: There is nothing better during the holiday season than a throwback to the classics. With this grape vine spray wreath accentuated with garland, white tipped small pine cones, and deep red berries, your home will be brought back to the classical feeling of the season.

name: Live Oak Love Wreath
description: These two east coast girls have fallen in love with Texas through the craggly beauty of the prevalent Live Oak tree. In our area we have been battling a cancerous disease called oak wilt. In dedication to these amazing trees we have created a straw wreath base covered in firm live oak leaves. We have used these leaves to show the strength and endurance of nature through all types of storms they endure. The leaves are very strong and have also been sealed; however, they are still leaves and are very fragile. If you choose to buy this wreath we will package it as carefully as possible, if it doesn't make the journey the way you had hoped we will reimburse you and pay the shipping to get it back to us.

name: The Gathering of Friends Cookbook — Volume One
description: The Gathering of Friends Volume One, was created to introduce food as a love language, enhancing traditions, fortifying relationships and celebrating life. Its unique style combines savory recipes and elegant designs in 16 stunning gatherings. Each chapter will leave readers prepared with simple recipes, original tablescape ideas, a ready-to-use shopping list, and inspiration to create their own ‘gathering of friends’.

name: The Gathering of Friends Cookbook — Volume Two
description: The Gathering of Friends Volume Two, was created to cultivate the idea of “food as a love language,” empowering the reader with simple ideas to enhance mealtime. It has five weeks of creative menu planning complete with shopping lists. Additional chapters feature effortless dishes, savory appetizers, garden fresh salads, hearty soups from the kitchen, and enchanting desserts: make this cookbook a splendid addition to every home.

name: The Gathering of Friends Cookbook — Volume Three
description:
The Gathering of Friends Volume Three, “Celebrations” was created to help us celebrate the seasons of our lives. Remember the summer fresh-garden herbs and vegetables and the familiar tastes of autumn apples from the orchard just down the road? Whisperings of winter, remind us of the cozy meals that once comforted and soothed. We need time to feast from tables set with traditions and to gather with those we love.

Life’s blessings are when we gather to celebrate the birth of a new baby, a graduation, a fiftieth birthday or a retirement feast. Simple, yet savory recipes that seem familiar to us from childhood are the heart of classic meals. As we savor these familiar aromas, the feelings from special gatherings from long ago are reborn, as old things become new again. When we gather with family and friends to celebrate life, it is a time of grace.

name: The Gathering of Friends Cookbook — Volume Four
description:
The Gathering of Friends, Volume Four, Celebrating Mother Nature, featuring the Gardens at Thanksgiving Point will draw you out of doors. These magnificent gardens have become a place of pilgrimage, brimming with the best of God’s creations. We hope you will treasure these gatherings and find peace and solace within what God has so freely given.

Our hope is that these refreshingly relaxed gatherings with simple, familiar tastes of the season will become some of your favorite sweet and savory bites. Blue skies, cool breezes, and fragrant foliage beckon us to gather out of doors. It is in the air, a time to gather and celebrate Mother Nature’s finest.  Outdoor dining summons hearty appetites. Relax in an oasis of peace and come gather at our table.

name: The Gathering of Friends Cookbook — Volume Five
description:
The Gathering of Friends, Volume Five, reminds us of the joy that comes from simply sharing a meal. Life is influenced by these tasteful moments together with family and friends. Every chance we have to gather around a table creates a cherished memory to be tucked away. Even old recipes can become new again.

We hope these satisfying menus filled with utterly delicious recipes will find a place at your table.

name: The Gathering of Friends Cookbook — Volume Six
description:
The Gathering of Friends, Volume Six,  A Year of Holidays at Home is an inspiring collection of delicious recipes and memorable menus. Celebrating each holiday is a wonderful way to toast each season and to create endearing memories.

There is nothing as magical as the anticipation of holiday celebrations. Much comfort and stability is derived from a table set with tradition. Join us, as we celebrate A Year of Holidays at Home.
